    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel your<strong> potato[es]</strong> and chop them into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/comforting-lean-beef-cottage-pie-with-sweet-potato-mash/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, reboil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, and dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/comforting-lean-beef-cottage-pie-with-sweet-potato-mash/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>, <strong>diced carrot </strong>and<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> beef stock mix</strong> and<strong> tomato paste</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and stir in your <strong>Marmite</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/comforting-lean-beef-cottage-pie-with-sweet-potato-mash/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have softened, increase the heat to high and add your <strong>mince </strong>to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>Once the beef has browned, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>to the pan</p><p>Season with a grind of<strong> black pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until slightly thickened and the beef is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>mince mixture</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/comforting-lean-beef-cottage-pie-with-sweet-potato-mash/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mince mixture thickens, return the<strong> drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong>, a splash of <strong>milk </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mash until smooth</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/comforting-lean-beef-cottage-pie-with-sweet-potato-mash/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mince mixture has thickened, transfer it to an<strong> oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Top with the<strong> mashed potato </strong>and sprinkle over the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden brown and bubbling \u2013 this is your <strong>mince cottage pie</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/comforting-lean-beef-cottage-pie-with-sweet-potato-mash/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While your cottage pie is cooking, reboil a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>broccoli</strong> into florets</p><p>Add the <strong>broccoli florets</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 4-5 min or until tender with a slight bite, then drain and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/comforting-lean-beef-cottage-pie-with-sweet-potato-mash/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> cottage pie</strong> with the<strong> broccoli </strong>to the side and enjoy!</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Loved this recipe? Keep an eye out for it on the Everyday Favourites section of our menu.</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
